<span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> The Top 35-under-35 competition recognises young CA(SA) achievers who are not only excelling in their professional capacity but are also making a meaningful contribution to society. Mathabo Makhaya, a chartered accountant by profession, is group financial manager of Harmony Gold Mine and chair of the Mineworkers Provident Fund. MoneywebNOW’s Simon Brown chats with Makhaya about her journey and being crowned the overall winner of the Saica Top 35-under-35 competition in 2022. Brought to you by the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants (Saica). Moneyweb does not endorse any product or service advertised in sponsored articles on our platform.